{"cards":[{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Object and image"},{"type":"headline","text":"Object: Source of light"},{"type":"headline","text":"Image: Reproduction of object"}]},{"lines":[{"type":"title","text":"Law of reflection"},{"type":"headline","text":"Incidence angle equals reflection angle"},{"type":"headline","text":"Angles measured between light ray, normal line"}]}],"definitions":[],"secText":["  <b>Essential Question: <\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>How can we describe objects reflected off of a plane mirror?","  <b>Enduring Understandings:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>Reflection<\/a> can be applied to types of waves, such as light and water waves. Reflection is the change of direction of a wave at the boundary between two materials, with the wave continuing in the original material.<br \/>2. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>Plane mirrors<\/a> are flat mirrors. In reflection, an <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>object<\/a> is the source of the light, while the <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>image<\/a> is the reproduction of the object. <br \/>3. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>Virtual images<\/a> appear on the opposite side of the mirror as the object. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>Real images<\/a> appear on the same side of the mirror as the object.<br \/>4. The Law of Reflection states that the <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='1'>angle of incidence<\/a> of a ray is equal to the angle of reflection of a ray.<br \/>5. <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='5' data-subsection='0'>Ray diagrams<\/a> are used to determine the position and type of image formed by the mirror.","  <b>Vocabulary:<\/b>  <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='1'>reflection<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>specular reflection<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>diffuse reflection<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>plane mirror<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>object, image<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>virtual image<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='0'>real image<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='3' data-subsection='1'>optical illusion<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='0'>light rays<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='1'>law of reflection<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='1'>incident ray<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='4' data-subsection='1'>normal<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='5' data-subsection='0'>ray diagram<\/a>, <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='20' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='5' data-subsection='0'>virtual ray<\/a>","  <b>STEM Skills:<\/b>  <b>    <br \/>  <\/b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='19' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>light<\/a>.<br \/>"],"objNames":["wb_image_concepts1","wb_law_reflection_concepts"]}